text: This is the first test of the new system that I have developed in order to help me make  YouTube videos in a more advanced way.
It uses an AI pipeline in order to interpret, spoken word, in recorded to a dot-wav file,  generates images, and then puts these images to slow Ken Burn Zoom and add music.
This should enable me to automate the process of making YouTube videos in an efficient manner.  I decided to make a YouTube channel because I was studying physics at the university and
I was beginning to become a little bit disconcerted with my studies and I wanted to give  myself creative outlet in a novel way.
Using the AI tools which are now so widely spread, I decided to try to develop a software  stack in order to do this.
I do not have any formal experience with AI engineering, but I have been automatically teaching  myself principles and concepts encoding which should help me do this task.
As of 4th February 26th, I am 24 years old.
